<br>
<font color=fff00>Why spend hours upon hours of leveling up to get the same exact excitment you can get from owning in a match of CTF or TF with your clan.</font><br>
<br>
I don’t think it’s the same as CTF or TF in that those are closed environments, always the same and very confined in their own respect. Its easy to learn the maps, they really aren't that big. Imagine a game of CTF or TF on a battlefield the size of West Karana (with lots more trees, hills, forts/keeps), that’s about one-third the size of the frontiers[PvP zones].<br>
<br>
When you login to a game of CTF or TF, both sides know the objective, what the other team is fielding(number of people) and exactly when the fight will start. In a battle of RvR, you have no idea if 10 players are invading you or 100 until you actually get in there, nor do you know when they’re coming. As the invader, you have no idea if you are about to take a fort completely by surprise (with zero player defenses) or if there are 20 Archers just waiting to take your head off when you get in range.<br>
<br>
<font color=fff00>will a GM be there to watch all the battles and award the people who showed the most skill a prize? will random items drop when a battle has been won? will a NPC spawn once the war is over that the winners can only engage that drops loot? how will people be rewarded other then some cheesy point system?</font><br>
<br>
If you're going to purchase Luclin, then you're diving into a ‘cheesy points system’ even more than you’ve been for the past 2 years. You’ll be able to trade your exp[read: cheesy points] for additional skills. What is gear? Gear is a series of items that enhance your stats, both primary and resist. Its all cheesy points, it’s always been.<br>
<br>
In RvR you accumulate Realm Points for killing people(you even get a point for being killed, participation is rewarded), these realm points can then be ‘traded-in’ for things just like in EQ(at least I think, no RP rewards were in beta). The way RPs were explained since the get-go was, people who participate in PvP will be better than those that don’t, the points can be turned into character enhancing abilities or additional stats. Everyone who PvP’s has the same ability to reap the rewards, not just people who win a /random or it was their day in the loot rotation.<br>
<br>
<font color=fff00>I see no end game, therefore to put days and days and days into leveling is futile</font><br>
<br>
End game is in the hands of the players for the most part, its what we make of it. Unlike the AI associated with big dragons, Dain or Tormax, players have the ability to alter tactics at the blink of an eye – we can think. A strategy that let you take a keep in 5 minutes today might get you wiped out in 2 minutes tomorrow, its not a nerf its player tactics and that makes for a more interesting end game to me any day. <p><b>Vendrix</b><br>
